Async await is a shortcode for promises and it removes the use of extra codes.

async simply makes a function return a promise.
await lets us wait for a function to finish before going to the next step.

NOTE: We can only use await when we are inside an async function.

NOTE: async await can only be used with promises, and it doesn't do anything with a callback

NOTE: The closest functionm to an await have to be async, even if we have a function inside an async function if we put await inside it won't work. The closest function have to be async.

FUN FACT: We can use await with promise.all as well.

async await{summary}:
It's a shortcut for promises.
lets us write asynchronous code like normal code.